title: Sally Oldfield-Water Bearer; early German CD pressing EAC FLAC
description:
This is an early German pression of this folky-new age album. Like her brother Mike, Sally is a multi-instrumentalist, playing spanish guitar, electric guitar, tubaphone, glockenspiel, mandolin, percussion, synthesizers, Moog bass, harpsicord, pipe organ....AND.....vocals. Sorry, no tubular bells or even Mike Oldfield on the album credits, although you never would have guessed. 

IMO, this is by far her best album
